1
00:01:27,000 --> 00:01:29,280
[Love Endures]
[Episode 23]

2
00:01:41,959 --> 00:01:42,680
Huang Yingzi.

3
00:01:46,879 --> 00:01:47,920
Why are you here?

4
00:01:48,719 --> 00:01:49,598
I'm here to fetch you home.

5
00:01:51,760 --> 00:01:52,359
Let's go.

6
00:01:58,959 --> 00:01:59,599
What's wrong?

7
00:02:00,079 --> 00:02:01,079
It's nothing.

8
00:02:01,840 --> 00:02:03,480
I'm just tired from work.

9
00:02:03,760 --> 00:02:05,200
I need you to recharge my battery.

10
00:02:08,439 --> 00:02:09,598
You can lie down, then.

11
00:02:17,120 --> 00:02:17,719
Who is this?

12
00:02:17,719 --> 00:02:19,198
Why is he sending you
messages late at night?

13
00:02:20,280 --> 00:02:21,159
No.

14
00:02:21,159 --> 00:02:21,918
It's an advertisement.

15
00:02:26,360 --> 00:02:27,159
Jiang Yi.

16
00:02:28,000 --> 00:02:29,560
I feel like something
is going to happen to Ding Ye.

17
00:02:29,680 --> 00:02:30,680
He's not responding on WeChat

18
00:02:30,960 --> 00:02:32,159
or replying to my messages.

19
00:02:34,039 --> 00:02:35,478
Why are you talking about Ding Ye again?

20
00:02:36,800 --> 00:02:37,800
Hasn't the reading event
that you organized for him

21
00:02:37,800 --> 00:02:38,719
already concluded?

22
00:02:40,360 --> 00:02:41,400
I think

23
00:02:41,919 --> 00:02:43,039
he's acting oddly.

24
00:02:43,759 --> 00:02:45,319
Isn't he always odd?

25
00:02:45,319 --> 00:02:46,319
No.

26
00:02:47,479 --> 00:02:49,360
It's different this round.

27
00:02:51,759 --> 00:02:52,519
Huang Yingzi,

28
00:02:53,400 --> 00:02:54,319
don't you think

29
00:02:54,319 --> 00:02:56,918
you're too sensitive about Ding Ye?

30
00:02:59,560 --> 00:03:00,400
I hope so.

31
00:03:00,400 --> 00:03:01,919
I hope that I'm just too sensitive.

32
00:03:13,719 --> 00:03:14,638
What's wrong?

33
00:03:15,520 --> 00:03:16,639
Are you upset?

34
00:03:23,240 --> 00:03:24,599
I'll be honest.

35
00:03:26,840 --> 00:03:27,919
I never once

36
00:03:27,919 --> 00:03:29,439
doubted our relationship.

37
00:03:30,000 --> 00:03:31,719
But sometimes I'd wonder.

38
00:03:33,159 --> 00:03:34,879
Did you choose to date me

39
00:03:36,479 --> 00:03:37,680
because

40
00:03:38,919 --> 00:03:40,919
you were already used to me?

41
00:03:41,759 --> 00:03:42,839
Or

42
00:03:44,080 --> 00:03:45,919
are you just

43
00:03:47,039 --> 00:03:48,319
missing the time

44
00:03:48,319 --> 00:03:49,560
we spent together?

45
00:03:49,560 --> 00:03:50,759
Jiang Yi.

46
00:03:51,479 --> 00:03:53,280
Why would you think so?

47
00:03:55,199 --> 00:03:55,879
Okay.

48
00:03:56,120 --> 00:03:57,360
Speaking of habits,

49
00:03:57,360 --> 00:03:58,120
I'm more used

50
00:03:58,120 --> 00:03:59,560
to being friends with you.

51
00:04:00,240 --> 00:04:01,400
Speaking of missing the past,

52
00:04:01,400 --> 00:04:02,000
I miss

53
00:04:02,000 --> 00:04:04,080
the days we spent together as a couple.

54
00:04:05,080 --> 00:04:05,719
I'm dating you

55
00:04:05,719 --> 00:04:06,759
as I love you.

56
00:04:06,759 --> 00:04:07,478
I like you.

57
00:04:07,479 --> 00:04:08,960
I want to be with you.

58
00:04:08,960 --> 00:04:11,280
This has never changed
since we were young.

59
00:04:13,039 --> 00:04:14,918
I thought you'd understand,
even if I didn't say it.

60
00:04:14,919 --> 00:04:16,120
How could you think like that?

61
00:04:19,480 --> 00:04:20,360
Fine.

62
00:04:21,560 --> 00:04:23,160
Be honest with me.

63
00:04:23,160 --> 00:04:24,519
What happened to him?

64
00:04:25,480 --> 00:04:26,600
Why are you helping him to this extent?

65
00:04:31,879 --> 00:04:32,879
I promised him

66
00:04:32,879 --> 00:04:34,120
that I wouldn't tell anyone.

67
00:04:35,120 --> 00:04:36,199
But rest assured,

68
00:04:37,360 --> 00:04:38,959
I'll surely tell you

69
00:04:38,959 --> 00:04:40,399
when I have the chance.

70
00:04:48,160 --> 00:04:49,000
Huang Yingzi.

71
00:04:49,279 --> 00:04:50,719
Perhaps to you,

72
00:04:52,079 --> 00:04:53,600
friends are more important.

73
00:04:53,800 --> 00:04:54,800
No, Jiang Yi.

74
00:04:54,800 --> 00:04:55,680
If that's so,

75
00:04:57,439 --> 00:04:58,600
let's go back to being friends.

76
00:04:59,040 --> 00:04:59,639
I'm leaving.

77
00:05:01,680 --> 00:05:02,519
Jiang Yi.

78
00:05:50,399 --> 00:05:51,120
Yingzi.

79
00:05:51,600 --> 00:05:52,480
Have you seen

80
00:05:52,480 --> 00:05:53,360
Ding Ye's latest news?

81
00:05:54,319 --> 00:05:55,439
News?

82
00:05:55,439 --> 00:05:56,319
The editor

83
00:05:56,319 --> 00:05:57,639
who exposed him
for harassing a female passenger

84
00:05:57,639 --> 00:05:58,920
has released new news.

85
00:05:59,120 --> 00:06:00,000
She managed

86
00:06:00,000 --> 00:06:01,560
to reveal Ding Ye's dark past.

87
00:06:01,560 --> 00:06:03,120
She even scrutinized your articles,
word by word,

88
00:06:03,120 --> 00:06:04,160
and interpreted the underlying meanings.

89
00:06:04,160 --> 00:06:05,800
It's going viral on the Internet.

90
00:06:05,800 --> 00:06:07,639
Unknown dark past

91
00:06:08,160 --> 00:06:10,279
of Ding Ye, an ex-best-selling author.

92
00:06:11,240 --> 00:06:12,600
The article even stated

93
00:06:12,600 --> 00:06:15,040
that he caused the death
of his best friend in college.

94
00:06:15,959 --> 00:06:16,519
No.

95
00:06:16,519 --> 00:06:18,040
How is that possible?

96
00:06:18,360 --> 00:06:19,920
This is completely nonsense.

97
00:06:20,560 --> 00:06:22,160
I'm not sure how credible this is,

98
00:06:22,160 --> 00:06:24,120
but the article's

99
00:06:24,120 --> 00:06:25,639
analysis seems well-founded.

100
00:06:25,639 --> 00:06:27,920
It satisfies the audience's imagination.

101
00:06:28,839 --> 00:06:30,240
I'll call Ding Ye.

102
00:06:31,079 --> 00:06:31,800
Don't be anxious.

103
00:07:01,639 --> 00:07:02,959
He's really weird.

104
00:07:03,240 --> 00:07:04,600
He gave me

105
00:07:04,600 --> 00:07:05,759
all the books in his collection.

106
00:07:05,759 --> 00:07:06,680
I had a glance at it.

107
00:07:07,000 --> 00:07:08,079
These books

108
00:07:08,079 --> 00:07:09,920
were sourced by him.

109
00:07:10,199 --> 00:07:11,199
Yet, he's giving all of them to me now.

110
00:07:11,319 --> 00:07:12,199
He doesn't want the books anymore?

111
00:07:12,399 --> 00:07:13,199
He said

112
00:07:13,360 --> 00:07:14,439
he wouldn't read it anymore.

113
00:07:14,879 --> 00:07:16,199
What else did he say?

114
00:07:17,160 --> 00:07:17,600
That's right.

115
00:07:18,040 --> 00:07:19,160
He has two books for you.

116
00:07:20,319 --> 00:07:21,000
Here you go.

117
00:07:25,839 --> 00:07:27,040
Has he ever acted like this previously?

118
00:07:28,480 --> 00:07:29,720
He's been a little strange recently.

119
00:07:30,079 --> 00:07:31,399
As an author,

120
00:07:31,600 --> 00:07:33,600
it's normal to face a writing block.

121
00:07:34,360 --> 00:07:35,720
Why is he so depressed?

122
00:07:36,160 --> 00:07:37,279
Did he tell you

123
00:07:37,279 --> 00:07:38,000
where he was going?

124
00:07:38,680 --> 00:07:39,399
No.

125
00:07:40,240 --> 00:07:40,959
Thank you.

126
00:07:40,959 --> 00:07:41,560
Thank you.

127
00:08:51,519 --> 00:08:52,200
Hello.

128
00:08:52,799 --> 00:08:53,480
Ding Ye.

129
00:08:53,480 --> 00:08:54,919
You're finally picking up your phone.

130
00:08:54,919 --> 00:08:55,960
Where are you?

131
00:08:56,399 --> 00:08:57,600
I'll go to you.

132
00:08:58,960 --> 00:08:59,679
Ding Ye.

133
00:09:02,720 --> 00:09:04,480
I know you've seen
the posts on the Internet.

134
00:09:04,480 --> 00:09:05,360
I saw it too.

135
00:09:05,360 --> 00:09:06,759
Don't bother these people.

136
00:09:06,759 --> 00:09:07,919
It's all nonsense.

137
00:09:07,919 --> 00:09:09,720
They did this for fame.

138
00:09:09,879 --> 00:09:11,360
I've completed the bucket list.

139
00:09:11,360 --> 00:09:12,399
Don't look for me.

140
00:09:14,480 --> 00:09:15,320
Ding Ye.

141
00:09:15,600 --> 00:09:16,080
Ding...

142
00:09:16,480 --> 00:09:17,000
Hello?

143
00:09:23,519 --> 00:09:24,559
(If, after we died,)

144
00:09:24,559 --> 00:09:26,079
(we ended up like a whale fall,)

145
00:09:27,840 --> 00:09:29,360
(nourishing the sea with its carcass,)

146
00:09:30,679 --> 00:09:32,279
(seeking peace on the ocean floor,)

147
00:09:33,080 --> 00:09:34,120
(death)

148
00:09:35,320 --> 00:09:36,879
(wouldn't be that scary after all.)

149
00:09:40,200 --> 00:09:41,080
The sound of waves.

150
00:09:47,559 --> 00:09:48,079
Come in.

151
00:09:49,080 --> 00:09:49,519
Chloe.

152
00:09:50,320 --> 00:09:51,080
I need

153
00:09:51,720 --> 00:09:52,720
your favor.

154
00:09:53,360 --> 00:09:53,840
Have a seat.

155
00:09:57,440 --> 00:09:58,120
What's the matter?

156
00:09:58,120 --> 00:09:58,960
What happened?

157
00:10:07,120 --> 00:10:09,000
I hope you can host a presentation

158
00:10:09,559 --> 00:10:10,279
about

159
00:10:11,200 --> 00:10:12,960
the encrypted part of Sky City.

160
00:10:14,679 --> 00:10:16,559
I was about to talk to you about this.

161
00:10:16,559 --> 00:10:17,639
Why are you agreeing to this now?

162
00:10:18,759 --> 00:10:19,960
I know,

163
00:10:20,960 --> 00:10:21,840
if I can't

164
00:10:21,840 --> 00:10:23,279
explain to the company,

165
00:10:24,080 --> 00:10:25,879
the project will be canceled.

166
00:10:27,120 --> 00:10:29,159
I don't have time to waste.

167
00:10:30,279 --> 00:10:31,120
Okay.

168
00:10:35,120 --> 00:10:36,000
That's all.

169
00:10:37,240 --> 00:10:38,320
I'll get going.

170
00:10:38,639 --> 00:10:39,120
Okay.

171
00:10:46,600 --> 00:10:47,200
Oh yes.

172
00:10:48,399 --> 00:10:49,559
This morning, Ding Ye

173
00:10:49,559 --> 00:10:51,439
suddenly transferred
all his earnings from his copyrights

174
00:10:51,440 --> 00:10:53,480
to a foundation.

175
00:10:53,480 --> 00:10:54,639
Strangely enough,

176
00:10:54,639 --> 00:10:56,120
the person handling the matter

177
00:10:56,480 --> 00:10:57,759
is a succession lawyer.

178
00:10:58,320 --> 00:10:59,360
He's still healthy.

179
00:11:00,440 --> 00:11:01,679
Why is he handling his will now?

180
00:11:14,720 --> 00:11:15,519
Jiang Yi.

181
00:11:15,919 --> 00:11:16,519
Where are you?

182
00:11:17,039 --> 00:11:18,759
I'm at the seaside in Jiangzhou.

183
00:11:19,000 --> 00:11:19,399
What?

184
00:11:19,399 --> 00:11:20,639
Your connection is poor.

185
00:11:20,639 --> 00:11:21,639
Which seaside are you at?

186
00:11:23,120 --> 00:11:24,159
No. Hello?

187
00:11:26,840 --> 00:11:27,240
Hello?

188
00:11:27,919 --> 00:11:28,720
Jiang Yi.

189
00:11:29,320 --> 00:11:29,720
Hello?

190
00:11:35,879 --> 00:11:37,399
Ding Ye.

191
00:12:32,720 --> 00:12:34,039
(When night falls,)

192
00:12:35,080 --> 00:12:36,240
(the lights in different brightness)

193
00:12:36,679 --> 00:12:38,079
(and different temperatures)

194
00:12:38,639 --> 00:12:39,480
(leave various traces)

195
00:12:39,840 --> 00:12:41,960
(on our retinas due to the distance,)

196
00:12:42,759 --> 00:12:43,759
(forming a picture)

197
00:12:43,759 --> 00:12:45,840
(of an ever-changing neon map.)

198
00:12:47,679 --> 00:12:48,839
He went to a high place,

199
00:12:50,080 --> 00:12:51,600
wanting to overlook
the city, yet he realized

200
00:12:52,759 --> 00:12:54,919
that the so-called
glimmering city lights

201
00:12:56,399 --> 00:12:58,000
had faded away.

202
00:12:59,559 --> 00:13:01,039
(Lu Dong could only see)

203
00:13:02,720 --> 00:13:05,039
(thousands and millions of noctiluca,)

204
00:13:05,440 --> 00:13:06,159
(repeating the cycle)

205
00:13:06,600 --> 00:13:07,399
(of flying,)

206
00:13:08,159 --> 00:13:10,000
(entanglement, competition,)

207
00:13:12,240 --> 00:13:12,960
and death.

208
00:13:21,960 --> 00:13:23,120
Special thanks
to the guitar accompaniment,

209
00:13:23,360 --> 00:13:24,000
Shi Xiaohuan.

210
00:13:27,279 --> 00:13:28,200
Ding Ye!

211
00:13:30,840 --> 00:13:31,840
Ding Ye!

212
00:13:38,039 --> 00:13:38,879
Huang Yingzi?

213
00:13:53,519 --> 00:13:54,960
Why do you come here?

214
00:13:58,639 --> 00:13:59,679
I'm worried about you.

215
00:14:01,279 --> 00:14:02,159
You're not upset anymore, are you?

216
00:14:04,159 --> 00:14:05,759
I'm sorry for saying

217
00:14:06,240 --> 00:14:06,960
harsh things to you

218
00:14:07,879 --> 00:14:08,559
and being petty.

219
00:14:09,440 --> 00:14:10,879
I should be the one apologizing.

220
00:14:11,639 --> 00:14:12,600
Let's not talk about this.

221
00:14:13,879 --> 00:14:15,320
Do you have news about Ding Ye?

222
00:14:18,720 --> 00:14:19,519
I tried to look for him

223
00:14:19,519 --> 00:14:20,960
but to no avail.

224
00:14:22,480 --> 00:14:23,600
I'm really worried...

225
00:14:23,879 --> 00:14:25,039
That he might commit suicide?

226
00:14:29,279 --> 00:14:30,039
Did you know?

227
00:14:32,799 --> 00:14:33,480
Chloe told me

228
00:14:33,480 --> 00:14:35,080
that he was handling
his assets for the will.

229
00:14:36,120 --> 00:14:37,399
I roughly guessed it.

230
00:14:37,399 --> 00:14:38,879
Are you sure that he's here?

231
00:14:39,840 --> 00:14:41,720
During my last call with him,

232
00:14:42,159 --> 00:14:43,679
I heard the sound of waves.

233
00:14:44,399 --> 00:14:46,279
I wanted to try my luck here.

234
00:14:49,120 --> 00:14:50,879
It's like looking
for a needle in a haystack.

235
00:14:51,759 --> 00:14:52,960
Don't you have other clues?

236
00:14:55,720 --> 00:14:57,240
He left me with two books.

237
00:15:02,720 --> 00:15:03,320
These books.

238
00:15:11,440 --> 00:15:12,159
What's this?

239
00:15:32,159 --> 00:15:32,720
Let's go.

240
00:15:33,600 --> 00:15:34,240
Hurry up.

241
00:15:36,440 --> 00:15:37,919
- Ding Ye.
- Ding Ye.

242
00:15:39,639 --> 00:15:41,360
- Ding Ye.
- Ding Ye.

243
00:15:49,279 --> 00:15:49,960
Ding Ye!

244
00:15:50,440 --> 00:15:51,159
Ding Ye!

245
00:15:53,039 --> 00:15:54,000
Ding Ye!

246
00:15:54,879 --> 00:15:55,840
Ding Ye!

247
00:15:56,960 --> 00:15:57,919
Ding Ye!

248
00:15:58,559 --> 00:15:59,319
Calm down.

249
00:15:59,919 --> 00:16:00,919
He might not be here.

250
00:16:02,159 --> 00:16:03,759
- Ding Ye.
- Ding Ye.

251
00:16:05,480 --> 00:16:07,200
Didn't I ask you not to look for me?

252
00:16:17,799 --> 00:16:19,559
You told me over the phone

253
00:16:19,879 --> 00:16:21,519
that you'd completed your bucket list.

254
00:16:22,639 --> 00:16:23,799
I thought...

255
00:16:25,039 --> 00:16:26,120
Didn't you ask

256
00:16:26,399 --> 00:16:27,759
if my bucket list was true?

257
00:16:29,519 --> 00:16:30,519
The list is real.

258
00:16:32,960 --> 00:16:33,799
But it isn't my bucket list.

259
00:16:35,480 --> 00:16:37,279
I have a childhood friend.

260
00:16:37,879 --> 00:16:38,799
His name is Shi Xiaohuan.

261
00:16:39,159 --> 00:16:40,319
I like literature,

262
00:16:41,519 --> 00:16:42,600
while he likes music.

263
00:16:43,000 --> 00:16:43,879
I know.

264
00:16:44,639 --> 00:16:45,960
He's your best friend.

265
00:16:46,559 --> 00:16:48,480
Well, where

266
00:16:49,919 --> 00:16:50,799
is Shi Xiaohuan?

267
00:16:54,240 --> 00:16:54,960
He's dead.

268
00:17:01,639 --> 00:17:02,399
It was a suicide.

269
00:17:03,559 --> 00:17:05,079
The time spent with him

270
00:17:05,480 --> 00:17:07,400
was the happiest moment in my life.

271
00:17:14,720 --> 00:17:16,240
(Xiaohuan's music
is really extraordinary.)

272
00:17:18,160 --> 00:17:19,720
(Accompanied
by the melody of his guitar,)

273
00:17:20,400 --> 00:17:22,119
(when I read the novels I wrote,)

274
00:17:23,598 --> 00:17:25,879
(the words appear deeper)

275
00:17:27,400 --> 00:17:28,400
(and more meaningful.)

276
00:17:32,200 --> 00:17:33,359
(Without his company,)

277
00:17:33,839 --> 00:17:36,119
(it's impossible for me
to get a spark of idea.)

278
00:17:39,000 --> 00:17:40,680
How's your new novel going?

279
00:17:41,119 --> 00:17:42,000
I think my first three books

280
00:17:42,000 --> 00:17:43,519
have used up all my ideas.

281
00:17:45,079 --> 00:17:46,319
I don't want

282
00:17:46,319 --> 00:17:47,720
to repeat my ideas.

283
00:17:48,240 --> 00:17:49,519
But I really don't know
what to write about.

284
00:17:50,720 --> 00:17:51,680
You can never find your true self

285
00:17:52,720 --> 00:17:54,559
without going through ordeals.

286
00:17:55,480 --> 00:17:57,559
You won't be able
to produce better work either.

287
00:18:02,960 --> 00:18:04,119
What if I couldn't

288
00:18:04,920 --> 00:18:06,960
be your reader anymore one day?

289
00:18:07,559 --> 00:18:08,079
Why?

290
00:18:11,200 --> 00:18:11,920
It's nothing.

291
00:18:13,640 --> 00:18:14,519
It's just

292
00:18:18,160 --> 00:18:19,400
that I want to travel.

293
00:18:21,000 --> 00:18:21,920
Do it, then.

294
00:18:22,799 --> 00:18:24,240
It's good to travel around the world.

295
00:18:25,640 --> 00:18:26,759
Have you seen Blue Tears?

296
00:18:28,279 --> 00:18:28,480
No.

297
00:18:28,480 --> 00:18:29,079
What are they?

298
00:18:30,400 --> 00:18:32,000
It's said that they are beautiful

299
00:18:33,319 --> 00:18:34,240
and surreal.

300
00:18:39,839 --> 00:18:40,839
(I didn't know)

301
00:18:42,599 --> 00:18:44,599
(that Xiaohuan had
severe depression all along.)

302
00:18:46,920 --> 00:18:48,319
(It was like any other normal day.)

303
00:18:49,359 --> 00:18:50,480
(I was still talking)

304
00:18:50,480 --> 00:18:52,039
(about my novel,)

305
00:18:53,519 --> 00:18:55,200
(while Xiaohuan
was quietly listening to me.)

306
00:18:56,880 --> 00:18:58,039
(Only then did I realize)

307
00:18:59,319 --> 00:19:00,519
(that he was saying his last goodbye.)

308
00:19:02,400 --> 00:19:03,039
(Xiaohuan left.)

309
00:19:03,960 --> 00:19:05,119
(He didn't leave anything behind)

310
00:19:06,119 --> 00:19:07,839
(apart from his bucket list.)

311
00:19:08,640 --> 00:19:10,240
So, your bucket list

312
00:19:10,680 --> 00:19:12,119
actually belongs to your friend?

313
00:19:13,000 --> 00:19:13,599
Yes.

314
00:19:15,359 --> 00:19:17,399
We wrote that as a joke
when we were little.

315
00:19:17,680 --> 00:19:18,880
Ironically,

316
00:19:19,960 --> 00:19:22,240
the playful list is now

317
00:19:22,680 --> 00:19:23,599
my only connection

318
00:19:23,960 --> 00:19:25,720
with Xiaohuan in this world.

319
00:19:26,799 --> 00:19:27,799
I spent a decade

320
00:19:28,759 --> 00:19:29,880
to complete the list.

321
00:19:30,359 --> 00:19:31,720
I thought I could finally let this go

322
00:19:32,000 --> 00:19:33,240
and somehow feel contented.

323
00:19:34,519 --> 00:19:35,960
However, as I stood in the sea,

324
00:19:36,960 --> 00:19:37,960
watching the vast ocean,

325
00:19:38,519 --> 00:19:39,799
with Xiaohuan in my thoughts,

326
00:19:40,319 --> 00:19:41,639
all I felt was the emptiness.

327
00:19:42,759 --> 00:19:44,240
A despairing emptiness.

328
00:19:45,640 --> 00:19:47,640
How do I navigate the days ahead?

329
00:19:49,759 --> 00:19:51,119
Can I face it?

330
00:19:52,680 --> 00:19:53,799
Should I face it?

331
00:19:56,359 --> 00:19:58,199
Should I just commit suicide
like Xiaohuan

332
00:19:58,200 --> 00:19:58,839
to end all the troubles

333
00:19:58,839 --> 00:19:59,440
since I have

334
00:19:59,440 --> 00:20:00,480
nothing to miss in this world?

335
00:20:11,880 --> 00:20:12,640
But I don't have the courage.

336
00:20:15,480 --> 00:20:16,759
After listening to your story,

337
00:20:17,559 --> 00:20:18,359
I don't know why,

338
00:20:18,359 --> 00:20:20,079
but I can empathize with you.

339
00:20:22,720 --> 00:20:24,000
I don't know why,

340
00:20:25,480 --> 00:20:26,599
but it feels like

341
00:20:29,920 --> 00:20:31,519
I've experienced this as well.

342
00:20:36,200 --> 00:20:37,000
All right.

343
00:20:37,480 --> 00:20:38,519
Since you've tried it,

344
00:20:38,519 --> 00:20:39,640
let's not trouble ourselves anymore.

345
00:20:46,160 --> 00:20:46,960
I mean,

346
00:20:47,279 --> 00:20:49,160
if your friend were still alive,

347
00:20:49,680 --> 00:20:51,160
he wouldn't hope
to see you in this state.

348
00:20:52,480 --> 00:20:53,319
He'd definitely hope

349
00:20:53,319 --> 00:20:55,000
that you could live a happy life

350
00:20:55,319 --> 00:20:56,720
and live a fulfilling life

351
00:20:57,200 --> 00:20:58,240
on his behalf.

352
00:20:58,599 --> 00:20:59,279
He's right.

353
00:21:00,200 --> 00:21:01,200
Your friend wouldn't wish

354
00:21:01,200 --> 00:21:03,039
to see you in despair.

355
00:21:03,920 --> 00:21:05,200
He'd certainly hope

356
00:21:05,200 --> 00:21:06,759
that you could write greater works.

357
00:21:08,920 --> 00:21:09,960
Without a reader,

358
00:21:10,799 --> 00:21:12,200
it's meaningless to be an author.

359
00:21:12,200 --> 00:21:13,400
Of course you have readers.

360
00:21:13,680 --> 00:21:15,359
You have a lot of loyal readers.

361
00:21:15,359 --> 00:21:16,799
I'm one of them.

362
00:21:17,839 --> 00:21:18,639
He is, too.

363
00:21:18,640 --> 00:21:19,839
He's your reader too.

364
00:21:22,039 --> 00:21:23,440
Have you ever thought about it, Ding Ye?

365
00:21:24,039 --> 00:21:25,039
Xiaohuan wanted

366
00:21:25,920 --> 00:21:27,759
to pull you out of the darkness,

367
00:21:29,079 --> 00:21:30,960
so he left you his bucket list.

368
00:21:33,559 --> 00:21:35,200
When I was just getting to know you,

369
00:21:36,000 --> 00:21:37,920
you looked really upset
with your poker face.

370
00:21:39,000 --> 00:21:40,880
However, after our roller coaster ride,

371
00:21:41,279 --> 00:21:42,079
aquarium trip,

372
00:21:42,519 --> 00:21:43,720
and sunrise,

373
00:21:44,640 --> 00:21:46,519
I noticed you'd cheered up.

374
00:21:48,160 --> 00:21:50,279
I guess that's the purpose
behind the bucket list.

375
00:21:59,880 --> 00:22:00,200
Well.

376
00:22:00,200 --> 00:22:00,599
Look.

377
00:22:01,720 --> 00:22:02,960
How gorgeous the sunset is.

378
00:22:03,799 --> 00:22:04,400
Am I right?

379
00:22:05,240 --> 00:22:06,000
Yes.

380
00:22:06,880 --> 00:22:08,359
Sunset and sunrise

381
00:22:08,880 --> 00:22:10,559
feel totally different,

382
00:22:11,519 --> 00:22:12,839
but they are both pretty.

383
00:22:47,319 --> 00:22:48,759
(The message changes every night,)

384
00:22:49,359 --> 00:22:50,599
(but there's no instruction)

385
00:22:50,599 --> 00:22:52,159
(to help Lu Dong find Zhang Fan.)

386
00:22:53,920 --> 00:22:55,279
(He runs not to search,)

387
00:22:56,279 --> 00:22:57,839
(as Lu Dong has no direction.)

388
00:23:26,799 --> 00:23:27,279
Let's go.

389
00:23:29,599 --> 00:23:30,279
Where are we going?

390
00:23:40,559 --> 00:23:41,319
Thank you.

391
00:23:43,160 --> 00:23:44,559
Your sudden presence

392
00:23:44,839 --> 00:23:46,000
makes me realize
that someone still cares

393
00:23:46,000 --> 00:23:47,559
about me in this world.

394
00:23:55,440 --> 00:23:56,440
Well,

395
00:23:56,880 --> 00:23:58,599
the world is still lovely.

396
00:23:58,720 --> 00:24:01,160
There is so much good food
waiting for us to discover

397
00:24:02,000 --> 00:24:04,400
and new friends we should get to make.

398
00:24:04,640 --> 00:24:05,119
Isn't that so?

399
00:24:06,519 --> 00:24:07,319
New friends,

400
00:24:07,319 --> 00:24:08,319
as in you?

401
00:24:12,640 --> 00:24:13,640
Can't we be your new friends?

402
00:24:24,119 --> 00:24:25,759
You don't have to thank me.

403
00:24:26,240 --> 00:24:27,720
We're even now.

404
00:24:28,119 --> 00:24:29,639
When I was at my lowest in high school,

405
00:24:29,640 --> 00:24:31,720
you replied to my letter
