00:27:46,680 --> 00:27:48,319
You're so huge. I found you right away.

493
00:27:48,319 --> 00:27:49,319
Hey!

494
00:27:50,400 --> 00:27:51,880
The coastline is so long.

495
00:27:51,880 --> 00:27:53,200
How did you find me?

496
00:27:58,920 --> 00:28:00,079
Didn't I tell you?

497
00:28:01,640 --> 00:28:02,680
No matter where you are,

498
00:28:03,640 --> 00:28:05,039
I'll surely find you.

499
00:28:15,319 --> 00:28:17,039
I don't want to play
the handkerchief game.

500
00:28:17,039 --> 00:28:20,000
That's for juniors in kindergarten.

501
00:28:20,000 --> 00:28:21,799
We're seniors now.

502
00:28:21,799 --> 00:28:23,519
What do you want to play, then?

503
00:28:23,519 --> 00:28:25,519
Let's play Eagle and Chicks.

504
00:28:25,519 --> 00:28:27,079
I want to be the almighty eagle.

505
00:28:27,079 --> 00:28:27,680
No.

506
00:28:27,680 --> 00:28:29,640
We're slower than you.

507
00:28:31,039 --> 00:28:32,680
Let's play Rubber Band Skipping.

508
00:28:32,680 --> 00:28:34,920
That game is for girls.

509
00:28:36,799 --> 00:28:38,720
Let's play Hide and Seek, then.

510
00:28:38,720 --> 00:28:40,480
The last person who's still hiding wins.

511
00:28:40,480 --> 00:28:41,720
I don't want to hide.

512
00:28:41,720 --> 00:28:43,680
If I stained my shirt,

513
00:28:43,680 --> 00:28:45,680
my mom would nag me.

514
00:28:47,160 --> 00:28:48,799
You can catch us, then.

515
00:28:50,160 --> 00:28:51,839
Fine.

516
00:28:53,519 --> 00:28:54,839
Ninety-nine.

517
00:28:54,960 --> 00:28:56,240
Ninety-eight.

